1.	Inside the **Content Browser** a new folder will be created containing assets related to the recorded sequence. 

	![](RecordedAssets.png)

	A **Level Sequence** as well as a folder containing an **Animation Sequence** based on the actions you performed. 


## End Result

You can now open the **RecordedSequence** asset and begin editing it as you would a normal Level Sequence (adding cameras, lights, effects, other characters and more). Below we created a sample scene with some cameras, a **Camera Cuts** track to cycle between the different camera angles, and a **Fade** Track to fade the scene in/out. 

